03/12/2006
BERLIN, Germany -- Chancellor Angela Merkel reaffirmed on Friday (December 1st) her country's continued support for Serbia's efforts to proceed on the road to Euro-Atlantic accession, but also stressed that full co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal remains the key requirement.
Meeting with Serbian President Boris Tadic in Berlin, Merkel noted Germany's interest in the stability of Serbia and the Western Balkans, and vowed to further assist the process using political and economic means.
(Vecernje novosti - 02/12/06;
Beta - 01/12/06)
